The paper deals with a cryptographic protocol for polynomial commitment and verification, which involves private two-party computation and information-theoretic guarantees. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the categories of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR), Information Theory (cs.IT), and Computing and Combinatorics (cs.CC).
